-- Spain's Santander posts 38 pct Q2 profit rise
-- 
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 02:08AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, July 31 (Reuters) - The euro zone's biggest bank Santander <SAN.MC> on Thursday posted a 38 percent jump in second-quarter net profit from a year ago, beating forecasts as provisions against soured debts fell.

Santander's net income in the period was 1.45 billion euros ($1.94 billion), compared to the 1.38 billion euros expected in a Reuters poll. [ID:nL6N0Q42W1] That took first half net income to 2.76 billion euros, up 22 percent from a year ago.